title: Total cross sections of 208-MeV and 315-MeV protons for light elements

x4freetext: Total cross sections of 208-MeV and 315-MeV protons

x4codes.hlp: University of Chicago, IL, United States of America
University of Chicago, IL, United States of America

x4freetext: Two 2.54 cm x 2.54 cm scintillators with
thickness of 0.635cm were used to define beam. A
placed coaxial with the beam defined by the first two
counters and at variable distance. It was connected
in anticoincidence with the coincidence output of the
first two counters to count directly the number
of particles removed from the beam. Thin scatterers
placed directly after the second crystal counter.
Correction for Coulomb scattering was made from
measured data at several small angles larger than
zero. Total cross section was obtained by extrapolation
of measured data to zero angle.
Internal beam scattered on internal Be target
